    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1899-09-18T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1899-09-18T00:00:00-05:00" n="497"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d497">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Buck</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Tokyo, Japan</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1899-09-18">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 18, 1899</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 353.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to append on the overleaf
                    reading of your telegram,<note n="1" xml:id="d497fn1">Printed ante.</note> dated
                    the 7th instant, to the effect that it would be agreeable <pb facs="0578"
                        n="482" xml:id="pg_482"/> to the United States if the Pacific Cable Company
                    of New York were authorized to establish cable communication between the United
                    States and Japan, and directing me to ascertain the attitude of the Japanese
                    Government toward a distinctively American cable.</p>
                <p>I to-day had an interview with the minister for foreign affairs, who appears to
                    be well disposed to the proposal embodied in the telegram herewith confirmed. He
                    said that he would refer the matter to the minister for communication, and then
                    to the full cabinet for their consideration. I will immediately communicate to
                    you the results as soon as known.</p>
                <p>I have, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">A. E. Buck.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
